getAutofillInitData.description: This is called inside an overlay (eg: on Windows or soon also on macOS) to retrieve available data

getAutofillCredentials.description: Used to retrieve a specific set of credentials

setSize.description: Used by Windows to communicate the desired size of the overlay to the native side

selectedDetail.description: Used by Windows to communicate a selected autofill item to the native side

closeAutofillParent.description: Used by Windows to instruct native sides to close any autofill overlays

storeUserData.description: Used to store Email Protection auth credentials (logging in)

removeUserData.description: Used to remove Email Protection auth credentials (logging out)

getIsLoggedIn.description: Used to get check if a user is logged in to Email Protection

getUserData.description: Used to get Email Protection auth credentials

getAddresses.description: Used to get both Email Protection addresses (personal and private)

refreshAlias.description: Used to refresh Email Protection private address and get both Email Protection addresses (personal and private)
